Neural Networks, Rule Learning. 

Neural Networks: The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks for learning symbolic rules. It compares the approach to traditional symbolic learning algorithms and highlights the advantage of neural networks in forming concept representations. 

Rule Learning: The paper specifically focuses on the extraction of symbolic rules from trained neural networks using the NofM extraction algorithm and soft weight-sharing training method. It compares the extracted rules to those learned using the C4.5 system and evaluates their accuracy and comprehensibility.
